Such a beautiful mild autumn, and perfect for experiencing the real Maremma: yes, the gorgeous beaches and rocky coastline of the Argentario, but also the lovely inland regions, the golden fields, rich farmland, the green hills and valleys and thick forests. There are miles of roads and lanes and hiking and cycling paths to explore, and all of it beautiful.

Just is special is the remarkable history of the region; the center of Etruscan civilization, ravaged by malaria and lawlessness for centuries after the fall of the Roman empire, war and political struggles for dominance throughout the middle ages, and it's remarkable reclamation and regeneration in the 20th century.

EFCC Arrests Two Suspected Internet Fraudsters at the Lagos Residence of Musician Skales 

In a recent operation, the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) apprehended two individuals believed to be involved in online fraud. The suspects, identified as Udemba Chukwuemeka (known as Jody) and Jamal Jamiu Onasola (known as Jamal), were taken into custody. 

The EFCC, in an official statement released on its verified platform, reported that the suspects had been engaging in fraudulent activities related to online romance scams. The operation took place on Tuesday, October 10, 2023, at House F10, Victoria Crest 4, Lekki, Lagos, which is the residence of Nigerian musician Raoul John Njeng-Njeng, widely known as Skales. 

The two suspects acknowledged Njeng as their mentor, with Chukwuemeka residing at Njeng's residence for two years and Onasola for a shorter period. Following the completion of the investigation, the suspects will be brought to court to face charges.
